RACE.FOOTNOTES: DONT FIGHT THE FED sped to the front in the two path, led along the inside then two wide on the far turn, kicked away in upper stretch and widened under a few taps of right-handed urging and coasted in nearing the wire. SHIP AND SCAM bumped with outer rival at the start, got put in a bit tight between rivals shortly after, trailed three then four wide early, went outside a rival on the backstretch, advanced four wide on the far turn, moved in midstretch and bested the rest. LOGON TO WIN was closet in pursuit four then three wide early, took aim two then three wide on the far turn, lacked the needed late kick in the stretch run and got outfinished for second. TORQUEWRENCH bumped with SHIP AND SCAM leaving the gate, stalked two wide between rivals, three wide on the far turn and could not respond when called upon. GIANOLA brushed the gate, rated on the inside, asked around the far turn and weakened. CHIPPEWA BUD was off slow to begin, ran up on heels while along the fence on the clubhouse turn, lost ground while still on the inside through the far turn and failed to menace. COPPERTUNITY rated three deep in the early going, lost positions in the middle stages, trailed two wide on the far turn, eased in the lane and walked off.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DEL MAR RACE 3 1M Dirt CR: 96. Starter Allowance Purse 43000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since May 24 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG HAT WILLIE antsy in the gate, stalked in the two path early, tipped out to launch a bid three deep midway around the far turn, took over past the quarter pole and cleared approaching the stretch, showed the way through the stretch run and held well in the end. CONQUERING KING pressed from outside in the three path, took over at the five-sixteenths pole, lost command past the quarter pole and chased the new leader two wide into the lane, stayed on through the drive to the inside of the winner, drifted out and checked in the final sixteenth and churned on for second. DUAL THREAT dropped back and tucked inside, lagged behind to the far turn, made progress along the inside then tipped to the two path around the bend and summoned a mild rally to earn the show honors. TELOS broke a step slow, tracked three to four wide on both turns and lacked the needed response. CARDIFF CRACK stalked from inside, chased out of range two wide into the far turn, spun three wide into the lane and came up empty. THIRTY FOUR COUPE took control in the two path while being pressured from outside, led along the inside to the second bend, lost command at the five-sixteenths pole and tired. THERE WAS STEWARDS INQUIRY AND AN OBJECTION PLACED BY THE RIDER ABOARD CONQUERING KING AGAINST BIG HAT WILLIE FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE LATE IN THE STRETCH RUN. FOLLOWING A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT CONQUERING KING CAUSED HIS OWN PROBLEMS BY SHIFTING OUT ONTO THE HEELS OF BIG HAT WILLIE AND THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE.
